==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[piece]] of [[eight]]|pl=[[pieces of eight]]}}

# An historical English term for [[peso]], a [[silver]] [[coin]], that was [[mint]]ed in Spain from the end of 15th century, equal to eight [[real]]es (hence the name).
#*''It was a long, difficult business, for the coins were of all countries and sizes — [[doubloon]]s, and [[louis d'or]]s, and [[guinea]]s, and '''pieces of eight''', and I know not what besides, all shaken together at random.'' — [[:w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], "Treasure Island".


